1.2 Installation via ‘package-vc’
=================================

Since version 29 from 2023, Emacs ships with ‘package-vc’ which teaches
the default package manager how to install packages from
version-controlled source repositories.  Keep in mind to regularly
upgrade thus installed packages with ‘package-vc-upgrade’ and
‘package-vc-upgrade-all’ commands.

   (Unfortunately, both ‘package-vc’ based approaches will byte-compile
the Elisp source files of all packages inside Nael's Git repository.
Just ignore the resulting compilation warnings.)

