1.2.1 Installation via ‘package-vc-selected-packages’
-----------------------------------------------------

In your Emacs session, load ‘package-vc’ and add entries to
‘package-vc-selected-packages’.  Install the selected packages by typing
‘M-x package-vc-install-selected-packages RET’.  Finally, make the
package selection permanent in your Emacs initialization file too:

     (require 'package-vc)

     (add-to-list 'package-vc-selected-packages
                  '(nael
                    :url "https://codeberg.org/mekeor/nael.git"
                    :lisp-dir "nael"))

     ;; Optional:

     ;; (add-to-list 'package-vc-selected-packages
     ;;              '(nael-markdown
     ;;                :url "https://codeberg.org/mekeor/nael.git"
     ;;                :lisp-dir "nael-markdown"))

     ;; (add-to-list 'package-vc-selected-packages
     ;;              '(nael-lsp
     ;;                :url "https://codeberg.org/mekeor/nael.git"
     ;;                :lisp-dir "nael-lsp"))

     ;; Call `package-vc-install-selected-packages' whenever modifying the
     ;; list of selected package recipes.

     (package-initialize)


