1.2.2 Installation via ‘use-package’ ‘:vc’
------------------------------------------

Since version 30 from 2025, Emacs' popular ‘use-package’ macro features
the ‘:vc’ keyword as interface to ‘package-vc’.

   (Because each package has autoload-cookies on relevant expressions,
and because ‘use-package’ will load each package's ‘*-autoloads.el’ file
that is generated at installation, you don't need to specify
load-triggers like ‘:mode’.)

     (use-package nael
       :vc ( :url "https://codeberg.org/mekeor/nael.git"
             :lisp-dir "nael"))

     ;; Optional:

     ;; (use-package nael-markdown
     ;;   :after markdown-mode
     ;;   :vc ( :url "https://codeberg.org/mekeor/nael.git"
     ;;         :lisp-dir "nael-markdown"))

     ;; (use-package nael-lsp
     ;;   :after nael
     ;;   :vc ( :url "https://codeberg.org/mekeor/nael.git"
     ;;         :lisp-dir "nael-lsp"))


